  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best questions to ask people to evoke wisdom?",
  "response": "Asking the right questions can stimulate deep reflection and evoke wisdom in conversations. Here are some thought-provoking questions to consider:\n\n1. **Personal Experience and Reflection**:\n   - What life experiences have shaped your beliefs the most?\n   - Can you share a moment when you learned something profound about yourself?\n   - What is a mistake you made that taught you a valuable lesson?\n\n2. **Values and Principles**:\n   - What values do you hold most dear, and how do they influence your decisions?\n   - How do you define success, and how has that definition changed over time?\n   - What principles guide your actions in challenging times?\n\n3. **Perspective and Insight**:\n   - If you could share one piece of advice with your younger self, what would it be?\n   - What do you believe is the most important quality in a leader, and why?\n   - How do you approach difficult conversations or conflicts in relationships?\n\n4. **Life Philosophy and Purpose**:\n   - What do you believe is the purpose of life?\n   - How do you find meaning in your daily routine?\n   - What legacy do you hope to leave behind?\n\n5. **Relationships and Community**:\n   - How have your relationships influenced your understanding of the world?\n   - What do you think is the key to maintaining healthy relationships?\n   - How can we foster a sense of community in a disconnected world?\n\n6. **Growth and Change**:\n   - How do you stay open to change and growth in your life?\n   - What practices do you engage in to cultivate self-awareness?\n   - How do you handle setbacks or failures?\n\n7. **Wisdom and Learning**:\n   - What is the most significant lesson you\u2019ve learned from a mentor or teacher?\n   - How do you continue to learn and grow as a person?\n   - What book or piece of art has had the most impact on your perspective?\n\n8. **Future and Legacy**:\n   - What do you hope the world will look like in the next 10 or 20 years?\n   - How do you want to be remembered by those you love?\n   - What are you most passionate about changing in the world?\n\nThese questions can encourage deep and meaningful conversations that allow individuals to share their insights and experiences, leading to a greater understanding of wisdom.",
